# Key Words
Episteme 
See Michele Foucault
Acknowledgement of Theoria or doctrine. Personal. Relative definition that is context bound.
EX: do you believe in x? Only tell you the episteme and its context not if it is true or false (a statement of irony, no doubt)

Physis
emergence, the form, the idea
![[Layer 4.png]]

Poiesis
The blooming of the blossom. The striving for immortality that is sought by most mortals. 
![[Layer 3.png]]

Praxis
Method, question, machine, generator, process.
Incarnation: machines, questions, tests, tools, social dynamics.
*One of the flaws is the singular nature of each node. The singleness should be replaced by making the node more explicitly contain any form that exists within its domain.*

Design
Incarnation: action in service of thought, anything physical, expression, excretion
Effect, offten the end goal of production. 

Doctrine (Nomos?)
Incarnation:  Laws are physical scientific law, relgion. 

Foam
The seemingly random and pre-existing CNodes that are drawn from, consciously or subconsciously 

Ecopoetics
Making sense of living on earth.

Theoria
Incarnation. No physical or material manifestation.
