Concept/consciousness Node (CNode)
A conception. Thought or action (ephemeral or physical). Reason or instinct (derivation blind). Cause or effect (non-temporal). 
With reference to poiesis, a CNode is like an element. Compound nodes eventually form bodies, from which poiesis occurs. 
*Note: Could chemical diagrams, which represent complex relationships and spatial relationships, be used to strong effect in communicating CNode relationships?* 


