			A process of solving problems through an indirect and creative approach, using reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involving ideas that may not be obtainable by traditional step-by-step logic.
			TRIZ: Altshuller, G. S. (1984). Creativity as an exact science: The theory of the solution of inventive problems. Gordon and Breach Science Publishers.
			A Russian acronym for the "Theory of Inventive Problem Solving," a systematic methodology for analyzing and solving complex problems by identifying and addressing contradictions.
