# Poiesis in Action
All thought is categorized into poiesis, more so the motion of thought between subject nodes. See the image that charts the motion between a presupposition (theoria), to an action, then an observation (praxis), then derived rules (doctrine), which feed back into praxis/theoria of questioning, then to design, each of which have their own different theoria, which fracture at another praxis point into ideologies, starting the cycle all over again until each derived ideology has enough of its own internal motion to be considered as an independent system no longer totally defined by the original steps of poiesis. 
![[Poiesis in Action.png]]
Classification systems like this are superior starting points for narrative generation. Such diagrams allow you to see the common columns, assumptions, and relationships between contrasting ideas. To represent, you apply the idea to situations. To parody, you move through and around an idea, contrasting it with its neighbors. To fracture an idea, you move away from some blocks while retaining others. To extend an idea, you examine the relationships between categories within it, create new ones, re-frame existing ones, and add more granularity to categories.
If a paradigm is a set of ideas (encompassed by the chart), a new paradigm introduces a new entity to the chart that forces all the other existing ideas to adapt to it. Adding a idea/column or dimension that becomes an essential aspect of defining each idea where no such dimension existed before. A paradigm shift is probably accompanied by both a new element and a new idea category. Whether or not the idea results from fracturing off from other ideas or is what forces existing ideas to recognize category is unknown. 
![[Morality Chart.png]]
Shifting is the movement between ideas. In the chart above, Classical -> Christian. What is to the "left" of classical or the "right" of contemporary values? What is between each of these generalizations? What is above, behind, or below? What overlaps? This is a question of how these relationships have been defined. If you have a binary set, there are only 2 digits possible, but if we were to convert the number into base 10, there are now many more completely different ideas expressible. Whether these ideas are the same thing written in a different way, as our number would be, or their appearance is total differentiation, depends upon the discussion. 10b2 is not 10b10, and 10b2 == 2b10 but they are not the same thing thought they might communicate the same information... 
